The language choices were definitely deliberate. I was envisioning a situtation like you sometimes find in local English/Spanish stations in the American Southwest, where the radio host will be speaking one language or the other and randomly shift to the other without pausing. Basically, the idea is that those broadcasts are coming from an area/reality where both languages are very prominent, to the point that it's assumed that everyone listening is fluent in both. As to why those radically different languages are both that prominent, well, that's up to you.

And thanks for the tip-off about not posting in the announcements thread. I completely forgot.








